Get Started with Einstein Report Formula Generation

Create row-level and summary columns in Data Cloud reports.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with Einstein 1 Sales Edition and Einstein 1 Service Edition.

If you haven’t enabled Einstein, follow these steps:

* Create a Data Cloud report, or select Edit on a Data Cloud report.
* Open the formula builder window by selecting Create Formula in the Fields panel, or selecting Add Summary Formula or Add Row-Level Formula in the Columns menu.
* In the formula builder window, select the Einstein tab.
* Describe the formula you want in simple terms in your natural language.
* Pass your request to Einstein by pressing Enter or clicking the send arrow.

After Einstein responds with a formula:

* Evaluate it for accuracy and safety.
* If needed, start over. Einstein isn’t conversational, and follow-up questions aren’t supported.
* Click Insert Formula if the formula looks good.
* Validate and Apply after checking the information inserted by Einstein.

Generative AI can produce inaccurate or harmful responses. Review the output for accuracy and safety.
title: Getting Started with Einstein Report Formula Generation
